==English==
===Etymology===
The final part of '''[[monadic]]''', etc.

===Suffix===
'''-adic'''

#{{mathematics}} {{computing}} When combined with prefixes derived (usually) from Latin or Greek names for numbers, used to make adjectives meaning "having a certain number of [[argument]]s" (said of [[function]]s, [[relation]]s, etc, in mathematics and functions, [[operator]]s, etc, in computing).

